OL,3,CMillions missing out on smart meter
OL,4,Cbenefits due to faults and poor service
OL,6,FIt has called for new rules to ensure
OL,7,Fenergy suppliers identify and fix
OL,8,Fproblems as quickly as possible,
OL,9,Fsaying it was particularly worried
OL,10,Fthat people could end up with huge
OL,11,Funexpected bills if their supplier is
OL,12,Fnot able to take an automatic reading
OL,13,Ffor an extended period of time.
OL,15,FCurrent rules allow suppliers to "back
OL,16,Fbill" customers for an entire year,
OL,17,Fwhether they have a smart meter or
OL,18,Fnot, but Citizens Advice want the
OL,19,Fperiod to be cut to six months to
OL,20,Favoid hefty catch-up bills.
