OL,4,Cbenefits due to faults and poor service
OL,6,FGovernment figures show that more than
OL,7,F10% of smart meters were not working
OL,8,Fproperly by the end of last year.
OL,10,FCitizen's Advice, wants suppliers to
OL,11,Fbe forced to meet new Guaranteed
OL,12,FStandards of Performance, which would
OL,13,Fensure timely diagnosis of issues and
OL,14,Frepairs, with affected consumers
OL,15,Fautomatically compensated if these
OL,16,Fwere not met.
