OL,6,FIt also wants consumers not to be left
OL,7,F"waiting in limbo" when suppliers
OL,8,Fblame issues on the Data
OL,9,FCommunications Company, which is
OL,10,Fresponsible for the smart meter
OL,11,Ftechnology, leaving smart users unable
OL,12,Fto get some issues resolved directly.
OL,14,FCitizens Advice chief executive Dame
OL,15,FClare Moriarty said: "The whole point
OL,16,Fof smart meters is to empower
OL,17,Fhouseholds to save energy and money,
OL,18,Fbut in reality millions are missing
OL,19,Fout on those benefits due to problems
OL,20,Fwith technology and poor supplier
OL,21,Fservice.
